<!--  CONTENT -->

<tr>
<td colspan="3">
<div id="sectionDescription">The Video Player is a multi-user tool for watching movies together. Movies can either be uploaded from a user's desktop or they can be access through a web link.</div>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-1.png" align="top">
Select "Object" from the Insert menu. Find and select "Video Player" in the Insert Object dialog and then click on the "Insert" button.
<div id="pix"><img src="Video/video-insert.png" width="200px"></div>
<div id="stepNoHang">
Alternately, if you have a video file on your desktop, you can drop it into the Wonderland window.</div>
</div>
</div>
</td>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-2.png" align="top">
To use the Player, right click on the window and select "Take Control."
<div id="pix"><img src="Video/video-takecontrol.png" width="200px"></div>
<div id="stepNoHang">
The window border will turn from red to green, a tool palette will open, and a "Release App Control" button will appear in the upper right of your Wonderland window.</div>
</div>
</div>
</td>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-3.png" align="top">
Click on the folder icon to load a video.
<div id="pix"><img src="Video/video-play.png" width="200px">
</div>
<div id="stepNoHang">
This brings up a window to enter a link to an on-line video.</div>
<div id="pix"><img src="Video/video-enterURL.png" width="200px"></div>
<div id="stepNoHang">
For example, you could load the BBC's <a href="http://www.bigbiodiversitycount.org.uk/Opalapplication/BBBC%20on%20the%20BBC.mov">Big Biodiversity Butterfly Count</a> video, or National Geographic's <a href="http://l3-hl1.videos02.myspacecdn.com/videos02/14/8c9f6d6048984c948a1fb3ef9d805422/vid.mp4">Meerkat</a> video by right clicking on one of these links, copying the link, and pasting it into the open video dialog.
</div>
</div>
</div>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-4.png" align="top">
Once you click OK, you will see a loading video message in the upper right corner of your screen. Once that message goes away, click on the Play button to watch the video.
<div id="pix"><img src="Video/video-BBC.png" width="200px"></div>
<div id="stepNoHang">
When done, click the "Release App Control" button in the upper right corner of the Wonderland window.
<div id="tipPix"><img src="2DApps/ReleaseAppControl.png"></div>
</div>
</div>
</td>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-5.png" align="top">
Here's what each icon in the tool palette does:<br><br>
<img src="Video/VideoIcons/icon-1.png" align="center"> Palette in-world / on HUD<br>
<img src="Video/VideoIcons/icon-2.png" align="center"> Open file or URL<br>
<img src="Video/VideoIcons/icon-3.png" align="center"> Rewind 10 seconds<br>
<img src="Video/VideoIcons/icon-4.png" align="center"> Stop<br>
<img src="Video/VideoIcons/icon-5.png" align="center"> Play<br>
<img src="Video/VideoIcons/icon-6.png" align="center"> Fast forward 10 seconds<br>
<img src="Video/VideoIcons/icon-7.png" align="center"> Unsync / Sync<br>
<img src="Video/VideoIcons/icon-8.png" align="center"> Drag out - <i>not implemented</i>
<br><br>
<div id="stepNoHang">
Use the slider under the tools to navigate to a particular point in the video.
<div id="tipPix"><img src="Video/video-slider.png"></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</td>


<!--       TIPS SECTION -->
<td>
<div id="sectionHead">Tips</div>

<div id="tipName">Video Player Uses</div>
<div id="tip">Use the Video Player to play recorded instructions, show educational content, or supplement training materials.</div>

<div id="tipName">Watching and Walking</div>
<div id="tip">Right-click and select "Show in HUD" to watch the video while you move your avatar around the world.</div>

<div id="tipName">Video Formats</div>
<div id="tip">The Player supports a wide range of video codecs and formats. For the complete list, please refer to this <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FFmpeg">FFMPEG information</a>. 
</div>

<div id="tipName">Why doesn't my video URL work?</div>
<div id="tip">When you enter a video URL, you must enter one to the video file itself. Many internet video sites send you to a web page that has a script that plays the video. Typically, but not always, video URLs end with extensions like ".avi", ".mov", ".mp4", or ".flv".</div>


</td>

</tr>
